For at least {= company_violation =}+ distinct environmental enforcement actions against named corporate entities by recognized government environmental agencies within {= event_window =}, name the company and the concrete violation, and supply a source (i.e., {= url =}+ URLs per action) on an authoritative-source page substantiating the enforcement action.

Requirements:
- The page must identify the claimed company as a named corporate entity. Municipal corporations and public utilities subject to environmental regulation count; generic references and individuals acting in personal capacity are out of scope.
- The page must describe a substantive environmental violation by the company — pollution, contamination, illegal emissions, waste / hazmat mishandling, environmental permit breach, or comparable ecological harm. Non-environmental enforcement (labor, securities, financial-disclosure, food-safety unrelated to environmental contamination) is out of scope.
- The page must establish that the formal enforcement action — fine, citation, NOV, settlement, consent decree, court ruling, or regulator's penalty announcement — was taken or publicly announced within {= event_window =}. Not the underlying-violation date; pre-announced future-effective penalties count when the announcement is in window.
- The page must communicate (possibly via URL among other things) that it is on a recognized government environmental agency surface or a directly-attributed first-hand journalism page that names the specific enforcing agency.
